        <c02 level="item" id="d1e192">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Georgine Milmine Welles</persname>, Auburn,
                  New York, to 
                  <persname>R. H. Lyman</persname>, Editor of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The World</title></bibref>, New York</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1909 Dec 7</unitdate>
            <physdesc>ALS, 1 p. w/env</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Expresses her appreciation for the review of her
                  biography about 
                  <persname>Mary Baker Eddy</persname>which appeared in
                  last Sunday's World.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e218">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Georgine Milmine Welles</persname>, Auburn,
                  New York, to 
                  <persname>R. H. Lyman</persname>, Editor of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The World</title></bibref>, New York</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1909 Dec 13</unitdate>
            <physdesc>TLS, 2 p. w/env</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[States that the criticism of her biography of
                  Eddy by Mr. Slaght at the end of his article in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The World</title></bibref>was valid as "the later events in
                  C[hristian] S[cience] history do need more thorough
                  treatment than I have given them." The remainder of
                  the letter explains why she did not go into greater
                  detail on some of the more recent aspects of
                  Christian Science and her plans for a later
                  edition.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
